The paper deals with the problem of information dissemination in networks with latencies, which is a fundamental problem in distributed systems and networking. The paper uses concepts from graph theory and combinatorial game theory to analyze the problem and derive lower and upper bounds on the cost of information dissemination. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with network information theory (cs.IT), as it studies the cost of communication in networks with latencies. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of Networked Systems (cs.NI), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY), as it deals with the analysis and optimization of networked systems.
